The paper deals with the degrees of freedom characterization of a multiple-input-multiple-output (MIMO) interference channel (IC) with rank-deficient channel matrices. This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves linear transformations and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also deals with communication engineering (cs.CE) concepts such as antenna configurations and channel ranks.
